          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are fork tender, add the<strong> drained butter beans </strong>and cook for a further 2-3 min</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p><p>Return to a low heat with a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and mash until smooth – this is your <strong>butter bean mash</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
